Select 1883-1920 &quot;Os6-6inch-County&quot; 
This selects all the 6inch maps together.
Rail tracks should be visible.
Still cannot work out how to feed in coordinates for historic maps.

Have just found &quot;Historic Six Inch Series (OSNI)&quot;
<a href="http://maps.ehsni.gov.uk/SixInchSeries/Default.aspx" rel="nofollow">maps.ehsni.gov.uk/SixInchSeries/Default.aspx</a>
Locate the &quot;Beacon (fixed red)&quot; jetty on the modern map.
Select &quot;Map contents&quot;
Select  &quot;Six Inch 4th Ed County Series &quot;
Untick the 10000 modern map.
Railway tracks visible.
Click &quot;i Identify&quot; and then click the map to get coordinates of that point.
